body:
Thanks for taking the time to report this.

What would you like added/supported?

**struct parametrization via virtual class parameter**

Can you attach an example that runs on other simulators?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)

Simplifies example from http://www.ece.uah.edu/~gaede/cpe526/2012%20System%20Verilog%20Language%20Reference%20Manual.pdf

```
virtual class C#(parameter type T = logic, parameter SIZE = 1);
   typedef logic [SIZE-1:0] t_vector;
   typedef T t_array [SIZE-1:0];
   typedef struct {
      t_vector m0;
      t_array m1;
   } t_struct;
endclass

module test_top ();
   typedef logic [7:0] t_t0;
   C#(t_t0,3)::t_vector v0; C#(t_t0,3)::t_array a0;
   C#(bit,4)::t_struct s0;
endmodule
```

```
%Error-UNSUPPORTED: Unsupported: class parameters
                                                            : ... In instance top
  108 | virtual class C#(parameter type T = logic, parameter SIZE = 1);
      |                                                      ^~~~
                    ... For error description see https://verilator.org/warn/UNSUPPORTED?v=4.203
```

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?
